parameters:
\SE[1]Look, I made a patch for you. I'll put it on for you,
so turn around.

Oh... I apologize... It would be nice if you could put it a
little to the left side...

Thank you very much, Messengers of Elysium. Please stay at
the inn tonight.

\SE[1]Won't you come and see my vigilante group tomorrow?
The captains should be back from their expedition by noon.
\SE[3]If it's around that time, I might have it...?

\SE[72]Yes, it's alright. \ After that, we'll immediately
return to Elysium.

\SE[0]Well then, let's do that tomorrow. \SE[1]Melissa's
vigilante group, huh...

\SE\SE[0]I'll raise my Melissa into the strongest army, so
it's best to get on her good side now!\.\SE[0] That's what
she said.

\SE[21]Hmm... the strongest army, huh. I wonder if I can do
it...
\SE[] (I wonder what she wants to convey.)

\SE[]Ronoa, you know. She said, I'm glad to see you after a
long time.

\SE Lunaroa seems to have taken a liking to this village...
The village chief is also kind.

\SE I might understand Lunaroa's feelings a little. Maybe
it's because this village reminds me a bit of Hatayaki
Village.
